# .git-blame-ignore-revs
# Commits listed here are ignored by git blame (via --ignore-revs-file).
# Use for pure-style commits (Prettier reformatting, import sorting, etc.)
# so that blame shows the real authoring commit instead of the reformat.
#
# Enable locally (once per machine):
#   git config blame.ignoreRevsFile .git-blame-ignore-revs
#
# Format: one full 40-char SHA per line. Blank lines and lines starting with # ignored.

